verdict.recommendation:
Replace `.send()` calls with a pull-payment pattern (withdrawal pattern). Instead of pushing ETH to recipients, record amounts owed in a mapping and let recipients withdraw their own funds. This eliminates the risk of silent send failures affecting contract state. Alternatively, use `transfer()` which reverts on failure (though this introduces DoS risk if recipients are contracts), or check return values and handle failures explicitly. The pull-payment pattern is the recommended approach:

```solidity
mapping(address => uint) public pendingWithdrawals;

function withdraw() public {
    uint amount = pendingWithdrawals[msg.sender];
    pendingWithdrawals[msg.sender] = 0;
    msg.sender.transfer(amount);
}
```
